    "Inappropriate choice of the problem category: The chosen metrics do not always reflect the biomedical need.",
    "For example, object detection (ObD) problems are often framed as segmentation tasks, resulting in the use of metrics that do not account for the potentially critical localization of all objects in the scene 15, 16 (Fig. 1a).",
